en_187504_0	The Chief Prelates of the main 3 Nikayas have written to President Maithripala Sirisena highlighting the prevailing challenges facing the Theravada Buddhism.
en_187504_1	The Nayake Theras have especially pointed out the damage being caused to the tradition and the genuine Bhikkhu community by certain persons who have been acting in the guise of Buddhist monks while being involved in wrongdoings.
en_187504_2	The Nayake Theras have emphasized in their letter to the President that it is high time the Bhikkhu Identity Card was regularized to expel such persons from the Buddha Sasana.
